What you need to know:

Djokovic, an eight-time champion in Melbourne, was widely harangued on Tuesday after reportedly issuing a list of demands in a letter to Tennis Australia that included moving quarantined players into private homes with tennis courts and getting them better mealsIn Wednesday's tweet, Djokovic said his letter to Australian Open director Craig Tiley had been taken the wrong wayDjokovic said he was merely speaking up for fellow players who were not being treated as well as him